$LNG['RULES_37']				= 'The non-compliance included in this regulation may result in a sanction on the offending account both the game and on the forum.       In addition, pursuant to the general conditions, an account and the « physical » user may be banned from all the services offered by Antaris Legacy temporary or definitive. An administrator or moderator can re-ban an account belonging to a user who is registered (bypassing the means of technical verification or not) despite its permanent or temporary banishment.<br /><br />        In case of violation of regulations, moderators and administrators of the staff are the only ones to decide the penalty to be applied.       In addition, the staff reserves the right to refuse and/or sanction anything that can harm the ethics or the development of the game.       Any conduct detrimental to the general atmosphere of the chat will be punished.<br /><br />        The duration of the penalty and the punishment applied only depends on the judgment given by the moderator.       The penalties vary: warning, temporary ban ranging from 1 day to several years or permanently and/or banishment from the chat.<br /><br />        The penalty can be challenged on the forum, in the "Complaint" section, the topic title should be written as follows : "Nickname challenge a sanction".       To be as fair as possible, the penalty assigned by the moderator will be reviewed by another member of staff, to the extent possible only.<br /><br />              Les comptes bannis ne peuvent pas être attaqués pendant toute la durée de la sanction. However, during the implementation of a sanction, the players account is removed from the first pause, if it is activated. This mode is not reactivated at the end of the sentence.       Its up to the player to pause itself after the ban period.';
$LNG['RULES_38']				= 'General chat is considered an optional service that can be removed at any time without the user to oppose it.<br /><br />              Therefore, a team member of Antaris Legacy, whether moderator or administrator may mute (that is to say, temporarily or permanently ban a player from general chat) without having to justify to of the user in question. The decision can not be contested since the « mute » does not prohibit the access to the essential elements of the account.<br /><br />              It is strictly forbidden to put the world coordinates (except home planet) on the general chat, and the composition of an army other than his own.       If you need to transmit, provide by private message or whisper. It is also prohibited to advertise any other browser game.';
$LNG['RULES_39']				= 'We want to remind that this is a game, keep a proper and respectable attitude towards other players in our community.<br /><br />        It is strictly forbidden to write insulting and/or disrespectful messages (discrimination, racism, homophobia, pornography).       Similarly, messages intended only to provoke insults from the interlocutor in order to make the ban is prohibited and punishable.       Some community members may be young teenagers, therefore, the words may offend the sensitivity younger and are not allowed in the game, like on the forums.<br /><br />        The rules above are valid also for nicks, planets names, alliance names, alliances descriptions, public messages (chat) and private (private message or alliance).<br /><br />        All threats coming out of the context of the game (the threats in the context of role-play are allowed) are strictly prohibited. The moderator is the only one who can fix the border / boundary between the role play and the « real ». It may take sanctions accordingly.<br /><br />        A player can make a complaint on the forum, in the "Complaints" section, if a players of the community is violating the rules listed in this paragraph.';
$LNG['RULES_40']				= 'Antaris Legacy is a game in constant evolution, it may happen that you meet any bugs or errors during your adventure.       These errors are to immediately report to the Forum in the "Bug and errors" section.<br /><br />        It is strictly forbidden to use bugs/errors to its advantage on pain of heavy penalty.       Non-disclosure of a found bug (beneficial or not) will also lead to a sanction.<br /><br />       If you have a bug, it is possible that an error message appears on your screen, to help us correct it as soon as possible, please save this message and forward it to the staff via the Forum.<br /><br />        The staff can not be held responsible for problems with a bug. The Antaris Legacy team does not reimburse losses to an error.       Only bugs during a Paypal or Allopass transaction will be refunded (after presentation of evidence: the Allopass code or PayPal transaction number).';
$LNG['RULES_41']				= 'It is strictly forbidden to use words or scripts to automate certain actions in the game. The user must use a standard browser to play on its Account (Mozilla Firefox, Internet Explorer, Safari, Chrome, etc ...). The use of add-ons is also prohibited.The game administrator can banish for life without prior notice, a player not respecting the formal prohibition mentioned above.<br /><br />        Users can create and use word/excel documents to back up data and/or coordinates of planets, however, it is strictly forbidden to scan the entire galaxy by automatic means.';
$LNG['RULES_42']				= 'In war, a player must wait at least 72 hours after the start of the war to leave his alliance (it is also forbidden to kick a player of his alliance during this period).       Also, a player can not leave the alliance between the time of the declaration of war and the beginning. Failure to comply may result in a sanction.<br /><br />       In peacetime, the player can leave the alliance at any time.';
$LNG['RULES_43']				= 'Any player has the right to decide to found an alliance, however, any alliance must respect the basic rules, like a decent name, correct home page with a text without provocation and without shocking images.<br /><br />        Any presentation of alliance, insulting or disrespectful (discrimination, racism, homophobia, pornography) will be subject to a penalty.<br /><br />        The founder is solely responsible for the content of the description of his covenant, and he will give the publishing rights only to people you trust.       If the description does not comply with the rules set out above, the founder of the alliance will be banned temporarily or permanently from the game.<br /><br />        Alliances can establish internal regulations, if it respects the rules of Antaris Legacy of French law, doctrine and morals.';
$LNG['RULES_44']				= 'The Staff may decide to set up a general truce over the world for several reasons:       <ul>         <li>for periods or specific days</li>         <li>following a maintenance that was not provided</li>         <li>following any bugs on attacks</li>       </ul>             At a general truce, no attack is tolerated, however, spying is authorized.<br /><br />              The system that handles the general truce only blocks the <u>start</u> attacks during the truce.       Therefore, the player has to cancel must manually space attacks started before the break and happening during it.       Failure to do so could justify filing a complaint by the player for non-regulatory attack.';
$LNG['RULES_45']				= 'An alliance can declare war simultaneously against 4 other maximum alliances.       Knowing that we can not declare war on an alliance already at war against 7 other alliances.       A war have a limited duration to be fixed between 14 and 31 days.       The declaration of war must be made 72 hours in advance of the forum.<br /><br />              In addition, there is a minimum period of 24 hours before the start of the war, where no attacks can be launched against a player from an alliance part of the declared war.       If a member of staff decides, this period may be extended without explanation. Similarly, wars dates may be changed by the moderator, if it deems necessary.<br /><br />        The rules of wartime attacks are the following :       <ul>         <li>A player can only attack 12 times in a 72-hour cycle, another player.</li>         <li>72h cycle it contains one or more 24 cycles.</li>         <li>The attacker may attack only 6 times a cycle of 24 hours.</li>         <li>The player can only attack once per cycle of 24 hours, the same planet via teleportation portal.</li>       </ul>        A war must be declared only by the founder of the alliance in question. If this rule is violated, the war may be canceled only by the decision of a moderator.<br /><br />              When the war is over, it is not possible to redeclare another against the same prior alliances within 14 days.       Alliances that are composed of only one member can not built a war (the founder can be sanctioned for non-compliance with this rule).';
$LNG['RULES_46']				= 'The attacks are prohibited to the following accounts :       <ul>         <li>In vactation mode.</li>         <li>belonging to a member of staff.</li>         <li>weaker or stronger than yours (limit high/low).</li>         <li>Multi-account with yours (same IP address).</li>         <li>ally with you (Auto Pact, member of the same alliance, etc ...).</li>       </ul>        You must respect the following rules of attacks :       <ul>         <li>A player can attack only 6 times in a 72 hours cycle, another player.</li>         <li>72h cycle it contains one or more 24 cycles.</li>         <li>The attacker may attack only 3 times a cycle of 24 hours.</li>         <li>The player can only attack once per cycle of 24 hours, the same planet via teleportation portal.</li>       </ul>   An attacks management system blocks any attacks that do not respect the rules above. However, please contact the staff in case of problems with the manager of attack.<br /><br />              It is strictly forbidden to bypass the attack limit high / low by making a loan to another player with the sole purpose of changing its points.       Any circumvention of this limit, and whatever the means employed, will be sanctioned by a member of staff.<br /><br />        Finally, the staff can set up a general truce on the server, following a maintenance that was not expected, or following any bugs on attacks. During the truce, no attack is tolerated, however, spying is authorized.';
$LNG['RULES_47']				= 'Any circumvention or blockages of the game, by any means whatsoever, is considered as a breach of regulations and therefore punishable.<br /><br />        non-exhaustive list of prohibited actions in the game :       <ul>         <li>Voluntarily increase the mass of resources exchanged between two accounts to be favored by 25% of allowed range.</li>         <li>Crash voluntarily troops and equipment on a stronger player.</li>         <li>The arranged attacks are to proscribe.</li>         <li>The triangular trade is banned (use third parties to overcome the blocking of accounts in multi).</li>       </ul>              A player bypassing the regulations may be subject to penalties up to definitive blocking of the account.';
$LNG['RULES_48']				= 'An « sleeping » account is stagnant (player no longer develops its behalf), used in the only goal of producing population, resources and equipment to send to the account of another player or a group of players. Any transaction of the kind is strictly prohibited.       Each player participating in such transactions is subject to banishment.';
$LNG['RULES_49']				= 'Trade between the two players must meet the following rates (with a 25% margin of error) to be fair :       <ul>         <li>Resources: 4 Iron units = 3 gold units = 2 Crystal units = 1 Elyrium units.</li>         <li>Device: just convert the unit price according to the above rates.</li>         <li>Population: 1 training unit = 20 units of Iron.</li>       </ul>        Exchange lasts a maximum of 48 hours. However, if at the end of this period, the exchange is  always unfair, then, the push system will give you an additional period of 24 to put you in good standing. After these 24 hours, if the exchange is always fair, you must apply for a push on the forum in the appropriate section.      A moderator will handle your request and treats subjects in each case, (it does not mean that you can be banned for non-compliance with the rule).<br /><br />        If you are in an irregular situation after an unfair exchange is completed (past 72 hours) and you have not made a « Push demand » on the forum, then the two offending accounts will be punished without notice.<br /><br />        Players have at their disposal a page letting them know if their trade is fair or not. To do this, go to the « Trade » page and the « Push » tab.<br /><br />        An account that is used solely to supply another, will be banned for life, and the « recipient » account will be punished in an exemplary manner.';
$LNG['RULES_50']				= 'During a break pact (between player or automatically), you must wait 24 hours before attacking your old ally.       Failure of the truce of 24 hours may result in a sanction.';
$LNG['RULES_51']				= 'Trade is only valid if there is an exchange between two players (the following rules do not apply to the use of the bank).<br /><br />        To transact business, you must first that both players have a pact. The pact can be automatic (that is to say, two players who are in the same alliance will not need to do pact between them in order to trade, as well, for two players who are in « wing » alliances).<br /><br />        It is strictly forbidden to send resources to a strong player without a fair return (respect for trade rate) in a period of 48 hours after the first shipment.';
$LNG['RULES_52']				= 'Antaris Legacy retains, for purely technical purposes, personal data from your account for a limited period of 10 days after the deletion request.       Your personal data is fully and permanently deleted from our servers after this time.<br /><br />              Nevertheless, you always have the option to request removal as soon as possible of their personal data by contacting the administrator via email address : staff@antaris-legacy.co';
$LNG['RULES_53']				= 'The staff reserves the right to read the messages, including messages exchanged between players, to verify compliance with the regulation.       That is to say, that the systems available in the game to communicate (eg, whispers in the "Chat" or private messages, etc ...) can be used against you in case of dispute.<br /><br />              By registering on one of our universe, you give permission to the staff to read all your messages.       This authorization is automatically canceled only by deleting your account.<br /><br />        If you wish to have private discussions with another player, you must use another form of communication : Skype, Msn, Facebook, etc...';
$LNG['RULES_54']				= 'The theft ofnickname is deliberate taking a username almost identical to another player of the universe in order to sow confusion.       It is strictly forbidden to attempt to appropriate the nickname of another player, even using some variants (or a few letters that are different but that look alike).       <br />Example: pseudo TOm with an "O" uppercase and pseudo T0m with the number zero.';
$LNG['RULES_55']				= 'The password is the security that prevents another person to log into your account, it is recommended to choose a hard to find (avoid putting your name for example), at least 8 characters with letters, numbers and special characters.<br /><br />        Your password should never be disclosed. The staff will never ask for your password. However, to make a loan account, you must provide your password to another player. The staff is not responsible in case of problems in this situation.<br /><br />        The passwords are encrypted by our servers. Therefore, the accounts can be hacked only in case the password is too simple.';
$LNG['RULES_56']				= 'The vacation mode is activated via the « profile » of the account. The minimum duration of the vacation is 72 hours. You must wait a minimum of 48 hours before you can reenter vacation.<br /><br />              The break causes the cessation of production of all resources. However, constructions, developments and population of production continue to take place during the break.<br /><br />              The chains and fast modes are not paused, that is to say, that if you vacation mode for 4 days, then you will lose four days your activation mode.<br /><br />              Attacks, espionage and trade with a vacation account is impossible. Only attacks and exchanges fleet that are in progress when entering in vacation are completed.<br /><br />        It is strictly forbidden to enter vacation mode after performing an attack. You must wait a minimum of 1 hour between the last attack and the vacation mode.       Non-compliance of this rule may result in an complaint from a player following a sanction.';
$LNG['RULES_57']				= 'A player has the opportunity to lend his account to another player who is already registered on the same universe. However, the loan account must have a minimum duration of 48 hours and must not exceed the maximum duration of 14 days.<br /><br />        The lender must first apply for a loan statement in the appropriate part of the Antaris Legacy forum. There must be a member of staff has confirmed the loan before the « recipient » player connects to the account.<br /><br />        During the term of the loan, the lender does not connect to account,see Section of co-management (if the lender connects before the end of the loan he has stated on the forum, then it will prevent the same topic about the end of the loan).<br /><br />        The « receiver » player has the prohibition to start hostile military actions on behalf of which he temporarily occupies (attacks and espionage).       However, it is allowed to perform ACS-DEFEND via his own account. The lender is not allowed to transfer his army to the recipient.       Failure to do so could result in a sanction of this player.<br /><br />        The lender must trust the other player to make a loan account. The staff is not responsible for the actions to be carried out on behalf of the creditor (planet deletion, changing the password, or just the simple deletion of the account).<br /><br />        Finally, the loan account does not cancel the rules of multi-account, trading and joint management. An account that has been loaned can not be reappointed for a minimum period of the last loan period multiplied by 2 (that is to say, if you made a loan of 4 days, then it will take eight days before a new loan is possible).';
$LNG['RULES_58']				= 'Antaris Legacy authorizes the donation account. A person may give his account to another only under the following conditions : the donor wishes to stop playing or the donor and the recipient wants to exchange their account.<br /><br />              It is strictly forbidden to give an account against a well in exchange (unless another account). We recall that the account are owned by Antaris Legacy.<br /><br />        In addition, account donations must be declared prior to the forum, and of course, a staff member must be validated before the gift is effective.<br /><br />        The gift must respect and appreciate the rules set out above. A donation is completely validated once the account email address has been changed by a moderator.       The new owner will provide his email address by PM or email.';
$LNG['RULES_59']				= 'Co management is having more people connecting to the same account to play together. Co management is strictly forbidden on Antaris Legacy.<br /><br />        The same person account owner, however, can connect to various locations (different IP address). This is not regarded as the co-management.';
$LNG['RULES_60']				= 'To reduce cheating, the sanction bypass and multi-accounts, Antaris Legacy team reserves the right to block any account using a VPN, an internet proxy or other means to make an anonymous account.';
$LNG['RULES_61']				= 'A person can not have multiple accounts on the same universe. Two accounts are considered multi-account when they log onto the same IP address      (Same internet box, public access, cafe, Edge, 3G, etc ...). However, if both players do not connect in a period of 7 days via the same IP address, then the multi-account is automatically deleted. You can see the list of players with multi-account yours by going to the « Multi-Account » tab of the « Trade » page.<br /><br />        Members of the same family can play on the same universe of Antaris Legacy. They must accept the written rules in this paragraph, you do not need to declare it on the forum.<br /><br />        It is strictly forbidden to trade (whether direct or indirect, that is to say, carried out by an intermediate player),       to attack and spy on players entrance in multi-account. Non-compliance of this rule will result in a penalty. multi-account players can, however, be in the same alliance.';
$LNG['RULES_62']				= 'You can only have one account per world. The account must belong to a single person since the joint management is prohibited on Antaris Legacy.       If you are more to connect from the same internet access point, then, see you in the next paragraph : « Multi-account ».<br /><br />        Connecting via a mobile can cause multiple accounts with players you do not know.       Please refer once again under « Multi-account » for more information.<br /><br />        The account belongs only to its owner. The email address provided in the profile page identifies the owner at a loss password.       Therefore, when a donation account, please change the email address as soon as possible.';*/
